#8217;s breaking news blog, \u003ca href=\"http://thelede.blogs.nytimes.com/author/robert-mackey/\">The Lede\u003c/a>, for five years, and wrote a news analysis column, \u003ca href=\"http://www.nytimes.com/column/open-source\">Open Source\u003c/a>, from 2014 to 2016. His work is focused on making sense of events through the close reading of firsthand accounts, photographs, and video posted on social networks by witnesses and participants.\u003c/p>\n\u003cp>His writing has also appeared in the New York Times Magazine, GQ, Slate, and The Guardian.\u003c/p>\n\u003cp>As a television producer, he has looked at \u003ca href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mD61YTMiHnw\">the role played by soccer hooligans\u003c/a> in the war between Serbia and Croatia for Britain&#8217;s Channel 4, and spent a year and a half making a series of \u003ca href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MDVaW7CjH4Q\">video letters\u003c/a> from refugees for a United Nations-sponsored program broadcast in Sarajevo, Zagreb, and Belgrade during the wars in the former Yugoslavia.\u003c/p>\n","image_350":"https://theintercept.com/wp-uploads/sites/1/2018/04/r_3eMQ-M_400x400-1523651274.jpg","language":{"code":"en","name":"English","slug":"english"},"nicename":"robertmackey","pgp_file":"https://theintercept.com/wp-uploads/sites/1/2020/03/RobertMackey.asc","pgp_fingerprint":"FB79 2352 6F3C BA07 909D  766F 8F6C AB73 335F B9D8","pgp_key":"Robert Mackey Public Key","staff_sections":[{"name":"Current Staff","speakingId":"current-staff"}],"twitter":"@RobertMackey","url":"https://theintercept.com/staff/robertmackey/","user_group":"","user_title":"Senior Writer"}],"banner_videokey":"","bitly_url":"https://interc.pt/2wAv0RG","categories":[{"name":"Politics","slug":"politics","subtype":"subject"},{"name":"Robert Mackey","slug":"mackey","subtype":"blog"}],"comments_number":"0","comments_open":true,"content":"\u003cp>\u003cu>To get a sense\u003c/u> of just how much damage Donald Trump is doing each day, by making the daily White House briefings on the coronavirus pandemic mostly about himself, and distracting attention from vital updates on the public health emergency delivered by scientists, it helps to look at how very differently this is handled in other democracies.\u003c/p>\n\u003cp>\u003c!-- BLOCK(oembed)[0](%7B%7D)(%7B%22embedHtml%22%3A%22%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%20data-width%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EQuestion%3A%20What%20metrics%20will%20you%20use%20to%20make%20that%20decision%3F%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ETrump%20while%20pointing%20to%20his%20head%3A%20The%20metrics%20right%20here.%20That%5Cu2019s%20my%20metrics.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%5C%2F%5C%2Ft.co%5C%2FSIbO5N6Bqx%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%5C%2FSIbO5N6Bqx%3C%5C%2Fa%3E%3C%5C%2Fp%3E%26mdash%3B%20Acyn%20Torabi%20%28%40Acyn%29%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%5C%2F%5C%2Ftwitter.com%5C%2FAcyn%5C%2Fstatus%5C%2F1248699773751685120%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EApril%2010%2C%202020%3C%5C%2Fa%3E%3C%5C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cscript%20async%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%5C%2F%5C%2Fplatform.twitter.com%5C%2Fwidgets.js%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22utf-8%5C%22%3E%3C%5C%2Fscript%3E%22%2C%22endpoint%22%3A%22https%3A%5C%2F%5C%2Fapi.twitter.com%5C%2F1%5C%2Fstatuses%5C%2Foembed.json%22%2C%22type%22%3A%22twitter%22%2C%22url%22%3A%22https%3A%5C%2F%5C%2Ftwitter.com%5C%2FAcyn%5C%2Fstatus%5C%2F1248699773751685120%22%7D) --\>\u003cbr />\n\u003cblockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" data-width=\"500\">\n\u003cp lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">Question: What metrics will you use to make that decision?\u003c/p>\n\u003cp>Trump while pointing to his head: The metrics right here. That’s my metrics. \u003ca href=\"https://t.co/SIbO5N6Bqx\">pic.twitter.com/SIbO5N6Bqx\u003c/a>\u003c/p>\n\u003cp>&mdash; Acyn Torabi (@Acyn) \u003ca href=\"https://twitter.com/Acyn/status/1248699773751685120?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">April 10, 2020\u003c/a>\u003c/p>\u003c/blockquote>\n\u003cp>\u003cscript async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\">\u003c/script>\u003c!-- END-BLOCK(oembed)[0] --\>\u003c/p>\n\u003cp>In Greece, for example, the nation is briefed at 6 p.m. each evening by Dr. Sotirios Tsiodras, an unassuming professor of medicine who studied infectious diseases at Harvard and now leads the Greek government&#8217;s coronavirus task force. Tsiodras, \u003ca href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WLd1dnJyAG0\">often reading from his notes\u003c/a>, has been credited with helping to rally the nation to quickly accept a national lockdown that has, so far, \u003ca href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com/opinion/articles/2020-04-10/greece-handled-coronavirus-crisis-better-than-italy-and-spain\">been more successful than most\u003c/a>, largely by presenting the science in a calm, rational voice of authority. On the rare occasions when his level-headed facade has cracked &#8212; like a moment last month when he appealed to Greeks to protect their elderly relatives by staying at home &#8212; the impact has been all the more powerful.\u003c/p>\n\u003cp>\u003c!-- BLOCK(oembed)[1](%7B%7D)(%7B%22embedHtml%22%3A%22%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%20data-width%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EGreek%20chief%20epidemiologist%2C%20on%20being%20asked%20%5Cu201cwhy%20make%20a%20fuss%20over%20old%20and%20sick%20people%5Cu201d%2C%20broke%20down.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cu201cThey%5Cu2019re%20our%20mothers%20and%20fathers%3B%20grandmothers%20and%20grandads.%20This%20is%20my%20answer%3A%20We%20honour%20and%20respect%20everyone%20-%20them%20especially.%20Without%20them%20we%20have%20no%20identity%3B%20we%20don%5Cu2019t%20exist.%5Cu201d%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%5C%2F%5C%2Ft.co%5C%2FOhZm0BPVyW%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%5C%2FOhZm0BPVyW%3C%5C%2Fa%3E%3C%5C%2Fp%3E%26mdash%3B%20Alex%20Andreou%20%28%40sturdyAlex%29%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%5C%2F%5C%2Ftwitter.com%5C%2FsturdyAlex%5C%2Fstatus%5C%2F1241804208619356164%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255